\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 View All Groups:\
\b0 - The system will permit the role(s) with this permission to view and act on all students and all groups in the site in accordance with the other permissions that have been assigned to this role (e.g., Add, Edit, Remove).\ \
\b Note\'b9: \b0 Users in role(s) that are not assigned this permission may only view or act on an assignment if it is released to the group in which he/she is a member. If the assignment is released to multiple groups and the user is not a member of every group, then the user will not have permission to view or act on the assignment.\
\b Note\'b2: \b0 Users in role(s) that are not assigned this permission may only view or act on submissions if they were submitted by a user in a group in which he/she is a member. }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1038\cocoasubrtf110 {\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Grader permission settings:\
\b0 - If there is no Gradebook in the site, the system will not display this permission.\ - This Gradebook permission controls whether or not the role(s) with some variation of this permission can enter a grade and comments for student submissions. \ - The system will display the 'Customize' link for roles with the section.role.ta permission and the gradebook.gradeSection permission.\ - By default, if groups exist in the site, the system will display 'Assigned Groups' for role(s) with the section.role.ta and gradebook.gradeSection permissions. Role(s) with these permissions will have permission to enter a grade and comments for submissions from students in the user's assigned group(s). If groups do not exist for the site, the system will display 'None' and the 'Customize' link beneath 'None'.\ \
\b Note: \b0 The instructor may increase or limit the scope of these permissions by clicking the 'Customize' link.\ \ - If the Instructor clicks the 'Customize' link, the system will display the Gradebook's Edit Grader Permissions' helper (GPH-1).\ - The system will display 'All Students' for the roles with the gradebook.editAssignments, gradebook.gradeAll and section.role.instructor permissions. Role(s) with these permissions may enter grades and comments for any student in the class.\ - The system will display 'None' for roles that do not have the one of the above combinations of permissions and may not enter grades or comments for any submissions.}

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Permission\
\b0 - By default, users in role(s) with the section.role.ta permission and the gradebook.gradeSection permission have permission to grade submissions from students in his/her assigned groups. To change the default permissions, users with the site.upd permission may add Grader Permissions as described below. \b \
\b0 - If an instructor wishes to increase or limit the scope of a TA's grading permissions, he/she can do so via the Grader permissions. \b \
\b0 - The Grader permissions consist of the following options:\ * 'Grade' or 'View': The presence of the 'Grade' permission directs the system to display an editable 'Gradebook Details' section on the View \ Student's Submission screen (VSS-1). The presence of the 'View' permission, in the absence of the 'Grade' permission, directs the system \ to display a non-editable 'Gradebook Details' section on the View Student's Submission screen (VSS-1).\ * 'All Categories' or '<Specified Category>' (Does not display if no categories exist in the Gradebook): By selecting 'All Categories' the instructor \ is indicating that the user should have permission to view and/or grade all assignments associated with gradebook items in all categories, \ including the unassigned category. By selecting a '<Specified Category>', the instructor is indicating that the user should have permission to \ view or grade only the assignment(s) associated with gradebook items in the specified category.\ * 'All Sections/Groups' or '<Specified Group>' (Does not display if no groups exist in the site): By selecting 'All Sections/Groups', the instructor is \ indicating that the user should have permission to view and/or grade all student submissions. By selecting a '<Specified Group>', the \ instructor is indicating that the user should have permission to grade submissions from students in the specified group.\ \
\b Note: \b0 These permissions work hand-in-hand with the Assignments Beta permissions. The system will first check the Manage Submissions permission to see if the user has permission to view submissions in Assignments Beta. The system will then check the View All Groups permission to determine which student submissions to display to the user. The system will then check the Gradebook permissions and, if they exist, the Grader permissions, to determine if the user has permission to grade a student's submission.}
